  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Cavachon in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Cavachon is a cross of two HDB-approved breeds, the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel and the Bichon Frise, and falls comfortably inside HDB's small-breed rules, the same way our Cavapoos and Maltipoos do. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and every Cavachon we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase."
      bridge="Is a Cavachon HDB-friendly? Yes: both parents are named on the approved list and the cross sits well within the size rules. Mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
      citationLabel="Read HDB's guidelines on keeping pets"
